<p>
  Variables can be used to store and manipulate data. Data can come in different forms, called <em>data types</em>.
  Below are all of the most common data types in JavaScript.
</p>

<pre>
Number // 3, 4.6
String // "a", "apple"
Boolean // true, false
Array // ["apple", 3, false]</pre>

<p>
  There are three ways of declaring the name of a variable.
</p>

<pre>
var power = false
// vars can be used anywhere in your program, and can be changed to different values

let counter = 1 
// using let is almost the same as var, but the variable will only be able to be referenced in
// the same place it was defined

const pi = 3.14159 // constants cannot be changed after they have been declared</pre>

