<p>
  Arrays are a special data type that act as a container of other bits of data. The elements in an array can be any
  other JavaScript data type, including other arrays.
</p>

<pre>
var myArray = [100, "paint", [200, "brush"], false] // Example array</pre>

<p>
  Each element in an array can be accessed by using <code>[]</code>. Arrays are 0-based in JavaScript, so the first
  element of an array can be accessed by using <code>[0]</code>. This also works for setting an element's value.
</p>

<pre>
myArray[0] // 100
myArray[2] // [200, "brush"]
myArray[3] = true</pre>

